******
[2] Afghanistan
Date: Wed 28 Nov 2018
Source: Business Standard [edited]
https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/polio-cases-touch-20-in-afghanistan-118112800789_1.html


The number of polio cases recorded in Afghanistan has risen to 20 this year [2018] after a new case was confirmed in the southern region, the Ministry of Public Health said on [Wed 28 Nov 2018].

The latest case of wild polio virus was detected in Shaheede-e-Hassas district in the southern province of Uruzgan, bringing to 2 the number of the polio virus cases in the district, Xinhua news agency quoted the Ministry as saying.

The paralyzed 3-year-old boy had never been vaccinated due to his family's refusal to go for polio vaccination.

A total of 14 cases have been recorded in southern Afghanistan, and the 6 other cases reported in eastern Afghan provinces so far this year [2018].

Polio virus could be transferred rapidly, and the only preventable way was vaccination, the statement noted.

The ongoing insurgency and conflicts have been hindering the efforts to stamp out the infectious disease in the country.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This media report gives details on the advanced notice case of polio mentioned in the global report. Basically, the patient is a 3-year-old child with no history of having received any doses of vaccine due to family refusal to vaccinate. This is an unfortunate occurrence, but a similar story to other cases of WPV1-associated disease and cVDPV-associated disease. - Mod.MPP]
